From ccc612df78a1955a0f1ad3c6953c7a2876bba6cc Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 06:21:33 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 23/65] media: rockchip: rkvenc2: put CCU pdev lookup on
 success

Plain-language impact:
Successful encoder CCU attach no longer leaks the platform-device lookup reference.

Kernel details:
Balance of_find_device_by_node() with put_device(&pdev->dev) after enc->ccu/list setup has completed.

Source: split from patches/cleanup-draft after docs/11-bsp-audit.md verification.
Signed-off-by: Yi Ding <yi.s.ding@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
index 5c0134aba09d..0b3ebbf19204 100644
--- a/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
+++ b/drivers/video/rockchip/mpp/mpp_rkvenc2.c
@@ -2990,6 +2990,7 @@ static int rkvenc_attach_ccu(struct device *dev, struct rkvenc_dev *enc)
 	dev_info(dev, "attach ccu as core %d\n", enc->mpp.core_id);
 	mpp_debug_enter();
 
+	put_device(&pdev->dev);
 	return 0;
 }
 
